### 3.9 Machine Learning Studio (Advanced Model Visualization & Comparison)

**Enhanced ML Model Visualization Interface:**
- **Multi-Data Type Visualization Panel (Right-Side Panel):**
  - Dedicated right-side panel displaying different data types and visualizations simultaneously
  - **Data Type Categories:**
    - Numerical Data Visualization:\n      - Distribution histograms for numeric features
      - Box plots showing quartiles and outliers
      - Correlation heatmaps between numeric variables
      - Scatter plots for feature relationships
    - Categorical Data Visualization:
      - Bar charts showing category frequencies
      - Pie charts for category proportions
      - Stacked bar charts for multi-category comparisons
    - Time-Series Data Visualization:
      - Line charts showing trends over time
      - Seasonal decomposition plots
      - Moving average overlays
    - Target Variable Analysis:
      - Class distribution for classification problems
      - Target variable distribution for regression\n      - Imbalance ratio indicators
  - **Interactive Data Exploration:**
    - Click on any visualization to drill down into details
    - Hover tooltips showing exact values and statistics
    - Zoom and pan capabilities for detailed inspection
    - Filter data by selecting regions in visualizations
  - **Data Quality Indicators:**
    - Missing value percentage per feature
    - Outlier detection highlights
    - Data type consistency warnings
    - Feature importance preview
\n**Parallel Algorithm Execution:**
- Run multiple ML algorithms simultaneously
- Compare performance across all algorithms in real-time
- Automatic resource management for parallel processing
- Progress indicators for each algorithm training
\n**Regression Models:**
- Linear Regression
- Random Forest Regressor
- Gradient Boosting\n- XGBoost
- Ridge Regression
- Lasso Regression
- ElasticNet\n- Support Vector Regression (SVR)

**Classification Models:**
- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest Classifier
- Decision Tree\n- K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
- Support Vector Machine (SVM)
- Naive Bayes
- Gradient Boosting Classifier
- XGBoost Classifier
- AdaBoost\n\n**Intelligent ML Recommendation Engine (USP):**
- Analyzes dataset characteristics:\n  - Target variable type (continuous, binary, multi-class)
  - Class imbalance ratio
  - Number of features
  - Sample size
  - Categorical-to-numeric feature ratio
  - Missing value percentage
  - Feature correlation patterns
- Suggests most suitable algorithms based on analysis
- Provides reasoning for each recommendation
- Ranks algorithms by expected performance
- Warns about potential issues (e.g., overfitting risk, insufficient data)

**ML Pipeline Features:**
- Automatic train/test split
- Full training pipeline automation
- Hyperparameter tuning\n- Model comparison\n- Best model identification
- Cross-validation support
\n**Algorithm Execution Details Panel (New Feature):**
\nWhen user clicks'Use This Algorithm' button for any recommended or available algorithm, the system displays a comprehensive execution details panel showing:
\n**1. Pre-Processing Operations Display:**
- **Data Preparation Steps:**
  - Train-test split ratio (e.g., 80% training, 20% testing)
  - Number of samples in training set
  - Number of samples in test set
  - Feature scaling method applied (StandardScaler, MinMaxScaler, etc.)
  - Encoding methods for categorical variables (One-Hot, Label Encoding)\n  - Missing value handling strategy applied
  - Feature selection techniques used (if any)
\n**2. Real-Time Training Progress:**
- **Live Training Metrics:**
  - Progress bar showing training completion percentage
  - Current epoch/iteration number (for iterative algorithms)
  - Training time elapsed
  - Estimated time remaining
  - Real-time loss/error values during training
  - Convergence status indicators

**3. Algorithm-Specific Operations:**
- **For Each Algorithm, Display:**
  - Algorithm name and type (Regression/Classification)
  - Hyperparameters being used (default or tuned values)
  - Model architecture details (for ensemble methods, show number of trees, depth, etc.)
  - Optimization method (Gradient Descent, Adam, etc.)\n  - Regularization parameters (if applicable)
  - Cross-validation folds (if enabled)
\n**4. Step-by-Step Execution Log:**
- **Detailed Operation Timeline:**
  - Step1: Data loading and validation
  - Step 2: Feature preprocessing (scaling, encoding)
  - Step 3: Train-test split execution
  - Step 4: Model initialization with hyperparameters
  - Step 5: Training process start
  - Step 6: Training iterations with loss values
  - Step 7: Model convergence achieved
  - Step 8: Predictions on test set
  - Step 9: Performance metrics calculation
  - Step 10: Model evaluation complete

**5. Output Results Display:**
- **Comprehensive Results Section:**
  - **Prediction Results:**
    - Sample predictions vs actual values (first 10-20 rows)
    - Prediction distribution visualization
    - Residual analysis (for regression)\n    - Confusion matrix (for classification)
  \n  - **Performance Metrics:**
    - Accuracy (for classification)
    - Precision, Recall, F1-Score (for classification)
    - ROC-AUC score (for classification)
    - RMSE, MAE, R² Score (for regression)
    - Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE)\n    - Training vs Testing performance comparison
  
  - **Feature Importance:**
    - Bar chart showing top 10 most important features
    - Feature importance scores table
    - Feature contribution analysis
  
  - **Model Insights:**
    - Overfitting/Underfitting indicators
    - Model complexity metrics
    - Generalization capability assessment
    - Recommendations for model improvement

**6. Comprehensive Reports Generation:**
- **Automatic Report Creation:**
  - **Training Report (PDF/Word):**
    - Executive summary of model performance
    - Dataset characteristics and preprocessing steps
    - Algorithm selection rationale
    - Hyperparameter configuration details
    - Training process timeline and logs
    - Performance metrics with visualizations
    - Confusion matrix (classification) or residual plots (regression)
    - ROC curve and AUC score (classification)
    - Feature importance rankings
    - Model comparison table (if multiple algorithms trained)
    - Recommendations and next steps
  
  - **Prediction Report (PDF/Word):**
    - Sample predictions table (actual vs predicted)
    - Prediction accuracy analysis
    - Error distribution analysis
    - Outlier predictions identification
    - Confidence intervals (if applicable)
  
  - **Visual Performance Report (PDF/Word):**
    - All performance graphs embedded:\n      - Confusion Matrix
      - ROC Curve
      - Precision-Recall Curve
      - Feature Importance Plot
      - Actual vs Predicted Plot
      - Residual Plot
      - Learning Curve
      - Accuracy Comparison Chart
    - Graph interpretations and insights
\n**7. Interactive Execution Panel UI:**
- **Panel Layout:**
  - Left section: Real-time execution log with scrollable timeline
  - Center section: Live training metrics and progress visualization
  - Right section: Output results and performance metrics
  - Bottom section: Download buttons for reports and trained model

- **Visual Indicators:**
  - Green checkmarks for completed steps
  - Yellow spinner for ongoing operations
  - Red error indicators for failed steps
  - Progress bars for training iterations
  - Real-time metric graphs updating during training

- **User Controls:**
  - Pause/Resume training button (for long-running models)
  - Stop training button (with confirmation)
  - Expand/Collapse sections for detailed view
  - Download individual reports or all reports as ZIP
  - Save execution log as text file
  - Export results to CSV/Excel

**8. Post-Execution Actions:**
- **After Training Completes:**
  - Display success notification with overall performance summary
  - Highlight best performing model (if multiple algorithms trained)
  - Provide quick action buttons:\n    - Download Trained Model (.pkl file)
    - Download All Reports (PDF/Word)
    - View Detailed Performance Analysis
    - Compare with Other Models
    - Retrain with Different Hyperparameters
    - Use Model for Predictions on New Data
\n**Performance Analysis Graphs (Generated Separately for Each Algorithm):**
- Confusion Matrix (for classification)
- ROC Curve with AUC score (for classification)
- Precision-Recall Curve (for classification)\n- Feature Importance Plot\n- Regression Error Plot (Actual vs Predicted)
- Residual Plot (for regression)
- Learning Curve\n- Accuracy Comparison Chart (across all algorithms)

**Evaluation Metrics:**
- Accuracy\n- Precision
- Recall
- F1-Score
- ROC-AUC
- RMSE (Root Mean Square Error)
- MAE (Mean Absolute Error)
- R² Score
- Confusion Matrix values
\n**Download Options:**
- Trained model file (pkl or JSON format) for each algorithm
- ML reportdocument with all performance graphs (PDF or Word format only)
- Training execution log (text file)
- Prediction results (CSV/Excel)\n- Feature importance data (CSV/Excel)
- Performance comparison report (PDF/Word)
