  - Smooth number transitions when values change
  - Refresh on page load to ensure accuracy
\n### 3.12 Comprehensive Report Module (New Feature)

**Purpose:**
The Report tab provides a centralized location for users to download a complete, consolidated report documenting all operations performed across the entire platform, including Data Cleaning, Visualization, Dashboard, ML Studio, SQL Editor, and Python Editor activities.

**Report Generation Features:**
\n**1. Complete Project Report:**
- **'Download Complete Report' Button:**
  - Prominently displayed button in Report tab with distinctive styling (neon green background with white text)
  - Generates comprehensive report covering all platform activities in current project
  - Available in PDF and Word formats only
\n**2. Report Content Sections:**

**A. Executive Summary:**
- Project name and description
- Project creation date and last modified date
- Total datasets uploaded (count and names)
- Overall project statistics:\n  - Total rows and columns across all datasets
  - Total charts created
  - Total dashboards created
  - Total ML models trained
  - Total SQL queries executed
  - Total Python scripts executed
\n**B. Data Upload & Management Section:**
- List of all uploaded datasets with details:
  - Dataset name\n  - File format\n  - Upload date and time
  - Number of rows and columns
  - Data types summary
  - Sample data preview (first 10 rows)
- Data modeling operations performed:
  - Tables joined\n  - Join types used
  - Join keys and conditions
  - Resulting dataset details

**C. Data Cleaning Operations Section:**
- Detailed log of all data cleaning operations performed:\n  - Missing value handling:\n    - Columns with missing values
    - Imputation methods used
    - Rows/columns removed
  - Data type conversions:
    - Original and new data types
    - Columns affected\n  - Duplicate handling:
    - Number of duplicates found and removed
  - Outlier treatment:
    - Detection method used
    - Outliers identified and handled
  - Text cleaning operations:
    - Columns cleaned\n    - Transformations applied
  - Column operations:
    - Columns renamed, dropped, or created
    - Feature engineering steps
  - Date/time transformations:\n    - Date columns processed
    - Extracted features
  - Categorical encoding:
    - Encoding methods used
    - Columns encoded
- Before and after dataset statistics comparison
- Data quality improvement metrics
\n**D. SQL Editor Operations Section:**
- Complete history of SQL queries executed:
  - Query text with syntax highlighting
  - Execution timestamp
  - Query execution time
  - Number of rows affected/returned
  - Query results summary (for SELECT queries)
  - Data modification operations (UPDATE, DELETE, INSERT, ALTER):
    - Tables modified
    - Columns affected
    - Number of rows modified
- Saved SQL queries with descriptions
- Query performance metrics

**E. Python Editor Operations Section:**
- Complete history of Python scripts executed:
  - Script code with syntax highlighting
  - Execution timestamp
  - Script execution time
  - Console output and print statements
  - Generated visualizations (embedded as images)
  - Data transformations performed:\n    - DataFrame operations
    - New columns created
    - Rows modified or filtered
    - Aggregations and groupings
- Saved Python scripts with descriptions
- Script performance metrics

**F. Visualization Section:**
- Complete catalog of all charts created:
  - Chart name and type
  - Source dataset
  - Chart configuration details:\n    - X-axis and Y-axis columns
    - Aggregation functions used
    - Filters applied
    - Color scheme\n  - High-resolution chart image embedded
  - Chart creation date and last modified date
- Chart performance and insights:\n  - Data points visualized
  - Key trends identified
\n**G. Dashboard Section:**\n- Complete catalog of all dashboards created:
  - Dashboard name and description
  - Dashboard layout screenshot (high-resolution)
  - List of charts included in dashboard
  - Global filters applied:\n    - Filter types and values
    - Date ranges
  - Dashboard creation date and last modified date
  - Dashboard interactivity features used
\n**H. Machine Learning Section:**
- Complete ML training history:
  - For each ML model trained:
    - Algorithm name and type (Regression/Classification)
    - Dataset used for training
    - Target variable\n    - Features used
    - Train-test split ratio
    - Hyperparameters configured
    - Training duration
    - Performance metrics:\n      - Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score (classification)
      - RMSE, MAE, R² Score (regression)
    - Confusion matrix (classification)
    - Feature importance rankings
    - All performance graphs embedded:\n      - ROC Curve
      - Precision-Recall Curve
      - Actual vs Predicted Plot
      - Residual Plot
      - Learning Curve
    - Model insights and recommendations
    - Training execution log
- Model comparison table (if multiple models trained):
  - Side-by-side performance comparison
  - Best model identification
\n**I. Project Timeline:**
- Chronological timeline of all operations performed:\n  - Data uploads\n  - Data cleaning operations
  - SQL queries executed
  - Python scripts executed\n  - Charts created
  - Dashboards created
  - ML models trained
- Visual timeline graph showing activity distribution

**J. Recommendations & Next Steps:**
- Data quality improvement suggestions
- Additional analysis recommendations
- Model optimization suggestions
- Feature engineering ideas
\n**3. Report Customization Options:**
