\n## 6. Design Style\n
**UI Framework:**
- TailwindCSS or Material UI implementation
\n**Color Scheme:**
- Primary Colors: Navy blue (#1e3a5f, #2c5282) for headers, sidebar, and primary buttons
- Secondary Colors: Teal (#14b8a6, #0d9488) for accents, highlights, and interactive elements
- Background Colors: Charcoal (#2d3748, #1a202c) for dark mode backgrounds, White (#ffffff, #f7fafc) for light mode
- Accent Colors: Neon cyan (#06b6d4), neon green (#10b981) for call-to-action buttons, notifications, and data highlights
- Purple Highlights: Purple (#9333ea, #a855f7) for dataset selection dropdown and interactive elements in Data Cleaning and Visualization modules
- Text Colors: White/light gray for dark backgrounds, dark gray/black for light backgrounds

**Visual Design Elements:**
- Clean, modern data-science aesthetic with professional appearance
- Application Name Background: Navy-to-teal gradient or textured background for'InsightFlow AI' branding in header
- Glass-effect panels with subtle transparency and backdrop blur for cards and modals
- Smooth transitions and micro-animations for interactions
- Collapsible sidebar navigation with icons and labels
- PowerBI-inspired modern interface aesthetic with data-focused layout

**Theme Options:**
- Light mode: White backgrounds with navy/teal accents
- Dark mode: Charcoal backgrounds with neon cyan/green accents and purple highlights
\n**Typography & Spacing:**
- Clear, readable sans-serif fonts (Inter or Roboto family)
- Generous padding and consistent spacing hierarchy
- Proper visual separation between functional sections
- Bold headings with navy or teal colors
\n**Chart Styling:**
- Vibrant, distinguishable color palettes for data visualization
- Consistent styling across all chart types\n- Interactive hover states and tooltips
- User-customizable colors for personalized data representation
- Teal and neon accents for highlighted data points
- KPI cards with large, bold numeric displays and customizable backgrounds

**Code Editor Styling:**
